<item>
            <title>[CXF-3051] Rename all POM properties that change dependency versions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3051</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The maven gang discourages:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;version&amp;gt;${blah}&amp;lt;/version&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One reason is that maven does &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; resolve these references before publishing a pom in the release process. Our released poms contain property definitions and dependencies that use them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If, for example, a user innocently create a setting for jetty.version that is, oh, for jetty version 8, maven will forget, entirely that we carefully declared a dependency on version 7.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix we can live with is to make all of these properties have names of the form cxf-*, so that other people won&apos;t accidently set them.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
